<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <%- include('partials/head') %>

  <body>
    <div id="main_div">
      <%- include('partials/header') %> <%- include('partials/nav') %>

      <main class="grid-layout">
        <%- include('partials/left-sidebar') %>

        <section class="page_content">
          <h2>Internet Slang</h2>

          <figure>
            <img src="/img/chatroom.gif" class="computer-gif" alt="Chat room" />
            <figcaption>
              Chat rooms and instant messaging introduced many of the
              abbreviations that are still used online today.
            </figcaption>
          </figure>

          <p>
            Before smartphones and social media, people spent hours chatting in
            AOL Instant Messenger, MSN Messenger, IRC, and online forums. Since
            typing quickly was important, many users shortened common phrases
            into abbreviations. Some of these terms are still popular today.
          </p>

          <table class="slang-table">
            <tr>
              <th>Slang</th>
              <th>Meaning</th>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td>LOL</td>
              <td>Laugh Out Loud</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td>BRB</td>
              <td>Be Right Back</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td>AFK</td>
              <td>Away From Keyboard</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td>TTYL</td>
              <td>Talk To You Later</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td>OMG</td>
              <td>Oh My God</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td>ROFL</td>
              <td>Rolling On the Floor Laughing</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td>L33T</td>
              <td>"Elite" written using numbers and symbols</td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td>ASL?</td>
              <td>Age / Sex / Location?</td>
            </tr>
          </table>

          <p>
            Although Internet communication has changed over the years,
            abbreviations like <strong>LOL</strong>, <strong>BRB</strong>, and
            <strong>OMG</strong> are still recognized around the world. They are
            reminders of how online culture developed during the early days of
            the web.
          </p>
        </section>

        <%- include('partials/right-sidebar') %>
      </main>

      <%- include('partials/footer') %>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
